headline: Market Sell-Off: 2 Dirt Cheap Stocks That Just Got Even Cheaper
summary: The S&P 500 (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC) recently reached correction territory as the benchmark index fell by 10% from its recent highs.  Two stocks that have jumped back up to the top of my watch list are Capital One Financial (NYSE: COF) and SiriusXM Holdings (NASDAQ: SIRI).  Both already looked cheap before the stock market correction and look even more attractive now.
